===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Greek]] '''[[ενδοσκελετός]]''' (''endoskeletos''), from 
[[Ancient Greek]] '''[[ένδον]]''' (''endon'') "in, within, in the house, at home" + '''[[σκελετός]]''' "[[skeleton]]".
=== Noun ===
'''endoskeleton''' 

# {{anatomy}} The internal [[skeleton]] of an [[animal]], which in [[vertebrate]]s is comprised of [[bone]] and [[cartilage]].

